The paper discusses the use of neural networks in deep reinforcement learning, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), computer vision (cs.CV), and neural networks (cs.NE). Given that the paper proposes a new method for improving the performance and sample efficiency of deep RL algorithms, it is most likely to belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG), followed by artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), computer vision (cs.CV), and neural networks (cs.NE).
